# AutoForge

AI multi-agent project generation framework. 6 agents build complete projects from natural language.

## Commands

```
./setup.sh                              # Setup (macOS/Linux)
setup.bat                               # Setup (Windows)
source .venv/bin/activate               # Activate venv
python forge.py "project description"   # Generate project
python forge.py --status                # Show projects
python forge.py --resume                # Resume run
python tests/smoke_test.py              # 31-check smoke test
python forge.py daemon start            # 24/7 daemon
python forge.py queue "description"     # Queue project
python forge.py projects                # List projects
```

## Architecture

Pipeline: SPEC -> BUILD -> VERIFY -> REFACTOR -> DELIVER
Agents: Director (Opus), Architect (Opus), Builder (Sonnet), Reviewer (Sonnet), Tester (Sonnet), Gardener (Sonnet)

## Key Files

- forge.py: CLI entry point
- engine/orchestrator.py: 5-phase pipeline
- engine/config.py: Config + budget
- engine/llm_router.py: Model routing
- engine/agent_base.py: Tool-use loop
- engine/task_dag.py: Task scheduler
- engine/lock_manager.py: Cross-platform locking
- engine/git_manager.py: Worktree isolation
- engine/sandbox.py: Subprocess/Docker sandbox
- engine/daemon.py: 24/7 daemon + project_registry.py + deploy_guide.py
- engine/channels/: Telegram bot + webhook API
- engine/agents/: 6 agent implementations
- constitution/: Agent behavior rules (editable)

## Coding Standards

- Python 3.11+, from __future__ import annotations
- Async (async/await, asyncio)
- Type hints on all signatures
- pathlib.Path for file paths
- rich for terminal output
- Cross-platform (Windows + macOS + Linux)
- Path traversal prevention in agents
- Test with python tests/smoke_test.py
